description: Triangle in which k-th number (0<=k<=n) in n-th row (0<=n) is number of hexads in S(5,6,12) containing k given points and missing n-k given points.
references: F. J. MacWilliams and N. J. A. Sloane, The Theory of Error-Correcting Codes, Elsevier-North Holland, 1978, p. 68.
author: _N. J. A. Sloane_.
